# Portfolio Intelligence Bot

## Project context
- Docker-first Python 3.11 project: run via `docker compose`, not on the host.
- Personal Telegram portfolio intelligence bot (advisory only; no trade execution).
- JSON persistence under `/app/data` (config, portfolio, state, news cache).
- Services: `portfolio-bot` (Python app) and `ollama` (local LLM API).

## Stack
- python-telegram-bot, APScheduler, yfinance, httpx, feedparser, BeautifulSoup, filelock, pydantic, pydantic-settings

## Code standards
- Modular packages: `bot`, `collectors`, `analysis`, `scheduler`, `storage`, `config`.
- Small files, type hints on all public functions, clear docstrings, explicit error handling.
- JSON writes: atomic replace via temp file; mutations guarded by filelock sidecar locks.
- Do not invent unrequested features or rewrite unrelated files.
- Before implementing: propose a short plan. After implementing: summarize changes and follow-ups.
- Keep `docker-compose.yml` and environment variable names compatible when extending.

## Boundaries
- No frontend.
- Bot recommends only (review, hold, investigate); never auto-trades.
